snippet.textDisplay:
Ohai! For a change a few personal words. My name is Philipp and I started this channel almost seven years ago – you don’t know my voice but you have heard my words because I write most of our scripts.

Oh boy. This was a hard video to make. Gratitude felt vaguely risky to do as a topic. It has this aura of cheap Instagram hashtag self help stuff.

Some of you will hate this video deeply, and the thought of that made me pretty anxious writing it. Gratitude was not supposed to be a video topic originally. Just like the Nihilism and Loneliness videos, the script was based on personal struggles and part of the process of dealing with them. And so it felt right to make gratitude a video too.

But Kurzgesagt is not a self help channel, so we'll keep this sort of content at roughly one or two per year.

We hope they are helpful to some of you.

If you care for my take on how to practice Gratitude, we made a Kurzgesagt Gratitude journal to combine the science with practical tips. https://shop.kurzgesagt.org/

Please note: You don’t need to buy this or anything else to practice gratitude – you only need a pen, a piece of paper and 5 minutes.

Thank you for watching our videos and reading this comment. Being able to do Kurzgesagt means a lot. To me and the whole team. – Philipp

I see a way of how to achieve gratitude.

We need to enforce values that every world religion containts, make them sexy again.
I am talking about respect, brother-/sisterhood, Integrity, honesty and love. It is obvious that our lives are controlled by negative traits. Be beautiful, successful, sexy, desired. Show off your wealth on social media, show the people that you are better than them. I think we need a hard break from all these things that breed dissatisfaction and hatred. We need to understand that life is what happens every day outside and that our interactions with each other are what really give us happiness in life. Be respectful, tolerant, honest and show some love. A smile and a thank you is not going to kill you. Be humble and love the ones close to you. These are values that we preach for centuries but just have forgotten about. So weird.

snippet.textDisplay:
Many jobs are using negative reinforcement ("You're doing bad we take your things") instead of positive one.
So if you're not especially bad, nor good, you still are reminded you could do better, more, faster & shit. Constantly. Even those who are "the best" ones.
And that's where burnout starts.
Gradually you can't even do things you like.

So no, I'm not grateful for my job, that makes me burnt out that much, that I can't at this moment do anything except the job and being constantly tired as fuck.

snippet.textDisplay:
3 years ago was a bad year for me. An embarrassing and painful break up, my father passing away, and my grandmother soon after. Alot went downhill from there: loneliness, self-doubt, work performance, you name it. Then I tried this gratitude journaling out of the random blue. I hardly know the gist about it, but I know that i've been ignoring all the good stuff, even if its just one, lately.
I wrote an entry everytime I feel bad. All the things and people I want to thank. I even cried once when I finished.
It's been around a year since my last entry. I'm in a better place, and I am sooo glad this channel mentioned the method that helped me!!

snippet.textDisplay:
One can say that dissatisfaction can come from a hope spot that after a tedious or difficult event, something cathartic will arrive, but didn't. At the least one can be grateful not for the results, but the realizing that you managed to endure, and that's really something.

One doesn't need to lower their standards to appreciate things; they only need to see the good in things, and acknowledge that there is still a goal to strive for, for betterment. Dissatisfaction is not uncommon; but one can cope.

I try not to worry if I can't find myself able to repay the goodness I see in people towards me, because I know they're doing that because they're are friends.

I think this comment is too long, but at the end of the day, it's the small things, and some great things, that matters, and I think that's lovely.

snippet.textDisplay: Come to think of it, gratitude and i don't really get along. I'm not sure whether it is even a feeling that's in my repertoire. I don't like to be on the receiving end of favors because they usually either feel unearned, or come with the unspoken expectation of reciprocity. Gifts, for example. Christmas and stuff. I have made it very clear that i don't wish to partake in the exchange of gifts, and yet sometimes people get me gifts and get lowkey offended when i didn't bring them any. Bitch please, my gift to you is that you get to spend that money on yourself and buy something you actually want, and i will do the same myself. Or when we order takeout and one of us has to pay the bill, regardless of which one of us paid the bill, once it's paid, it's paid. I'm not keeping tabs on who owes who. Or if i'm going for a grocery run and a roommate asks me to bring milk, i'll bring the milk. If you want that milk, you better not try to offer me those couple of petty coins, i don't do cash, and i still don't keep tabs. If you want to bring me back like cookies or something sometime, that's fair, but that's on you. I'm not incapable of empathy, but i don't get along with gratitude. "debt of gratitude" has a very negative connotation to me, it's quite literally a debt, and i don't like to be in debt.

snippet.textDisplay: Changing your behavior by self reflection really helps. When I was in the 6th grade I was a bully, a jerk, and I had no friends. Now, in 8th grade. I’ve helped my one of my many friends deal with depression to the point where she’d cut herself, I’ve been told multiple times by people that their world was made a better place by me. And all of this, was when I realized how much life is worth. You only have one chance. Live it. Have gratitude. And be happy. No one is forcing you to change your life, and if you want change, don’t feel rushed. Just concentrate, relax, realize, reflect, and have Gratitude in anything and everything you do. You are an amazing person.

snippet.textDisplay:
There is only “ONE” Ultimate Truth. And it is this:

Every new thought that you have, is literally an exact negation of the previous thought!

And this applies to “ALL” your thoughts.

So each new thought that you have cancels out the previous one. It’s a negation. A cancellation, a contradiction etc.

This is because your mind/soul is made of eulerian sinusoids. Mathematical sine and cosine waves. And they always have to balance to zero. This is why you have a positive thought, immediately followed by it’s negative counterpart to create and maintain a value of zero (0). This is also why the soul/monad is dimensionless and not detectable by any scientific method.

Reality is all about creating and maintaining a zero level groundstate, because only that can be stable.

Go ahead and try paying attention to it next time you’re having a thought. And you will see that they always negate eachother. This is why you are always confused and this is why doubt exists. The previous thought is the answer to your current thought!

So you see..

It’s about understanding “WHY” you have the thoughts that you do!

Rather than engaging with the actual content of the thoughts. (Which is what every single human on this planet is currently already doing and has always done).

And once you become good enough at it, you can see that your current thought is always WHOLLY dependent upon the previous thought. The previous thought is what DEFINES the current thought.

So for example, you may think about something being a certain way.. and than boom! Immediately a thought arises in your mind that contradicts it! So quite literally, your mind is made of negations!

It’s all about opposites.

Why wouldn’t our minds work this way?

Why wouldn’t every new thought cancel and negate the previous one?

This is the true version of universal balance.

So your job is simply to become aware of it and to be able to see it clearly. And when you hit the limit of seeing it, you achieve enlightenment and gain the perspective of the mental frequency singularity outside space and time.

+-+-+-+-+- = 0.

I have checked this countless times. And it’s always accurate. This is the one thing that does not change or deviate in any way. It’s the one and only thing you can always 100% rely on.

It’s the truth that you can check for yourself.

So simply put,

Your mind is made of negations!

Even the negations themselves get negated. “Everything” gets negated. This is the only way that reality can ever be fair and all-inclusive.

This is what Hegel was actually talking about all those years back when he spoke about the “negation of the negation process” In fact, this is what Gnosis actually is.. The negation of the entire negation process!

If this information reaches enough people, it will cause a global shift in consciousness.
